  19,78,"Does he have knowledge of the Ghaib and therefore he said that with some proof? Or does he have a pledge with his Lord to enter him into paradise and to give him wealth and children?"
  19,79,"The matter is not as he claimed. I will certainly record what he says and does; and I will give him a punishment over and above his punishment because of the falsehood that he claims."
  19,82,"The matter is not as they claimed. These things that they worshipped besides Allah will reject the idolatersâ€™ worship of them on the Day of Judgment. They will disassociate themselves from them and become their enemies."
  19,86,"I will drive the disbelievers to Hell thirsty."
  19,89,"You - who say this - have indeed brought something monstrous."
  19,91,"All of this because they have attributed a son to the Merciful. Allah is high above that by far."
  19,92,"It is not befitting of the Merciful to take a son as He is pure of that."
  19,94,"He has full knowledge of them and has numbered them exactly. Nothing of theirs is hidden from Him."